            <h2>Best Practices</h2>
            <div class="content-grid">
                <p>Use when users donâ€™t have access to digital technology.</p>
                <p>If body copy MUST be 8pts., ensure that every other aspect of the document is as accessible as possible.</p>
                <p><span>If the document is letter sized, there must be a one-inch margin at minimum for text.</span></p>
                <div>
                    <!-- @import "img/printBestPractices1.kit" -->
                </div>
                <p>If display fonts are being used, repeat the content again in a more accessible font.</p>
                <p><span>Try to avoid using superscript or subscript text if possible.</span></p>
                <div>
                    <!-- @import "img/printBestPractices2.kit" -->
                </div>
                <div>
                    <!-- @import "img/printBestPractices3.kit" -->
                </div>
                <p>Do your best to use an off-white and matte paper in order to reduce glare.</p>
                <p>If possible, use a thicker stock to avoid show-through.</p>
                <p>Source: <a href="https://www.rgd.ca/database/files/library/RGD_AccessAbility2_Handbook_2019_06_01(1).pdf">RGD ONTARIO</a></p>
            </div>
        </article>
